{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17635931","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17635931"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T18:22:15+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T18:22:15+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17549"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17549","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17549"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.11,0.11,0.05,0.74,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10239"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75864"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10239","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10239"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17549"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61377"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4911"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4932"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23943"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23945"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75864","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/75864"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA skin condition is characterised by dry skin, fissure formation, higher risk of unrecognised thermal injuries, and denervation of dermal structures with decreased sweating.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following pathologies is being described?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Brachial plexopathy","Peroneal neuropathy","Hereditary neuropathy","Diabetic neuropathy","Ulnar neuropathy"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe described condition is \u003Cstrong\u003Ediabetic neuropathy\u003C/strong\u003E, which can lead to autonomic dysfunction. This results in decreased sweating and dry skin, increasing the risk of fissures and thermal injuries. Autonomic neuropathy affects the nerves that control involuntary bodily functions, including those that regulate sweat glands.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBrachial plexopathy\u003C/strong\u003E - affects motor and sensory functions in the arm, not autonomic functions\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPeroneal neuropathy\u003C/strong\u003E - Primarily affects motor and sensory function in the lower leg and foot\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHereditary neuropathy\u003C/strong\u003E - Can vary widely in presentation but does not specifically cause the described autonomic symptoms\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EUlnar neuropathy\u003C/strong\u003E - Affects motor and sensory function in the hand, not autonomic functions\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Diabetic neuropathy can lead to autonomic dysfunction, resulting in decreased sweating and dry skin.","Autonomic dysfunction in diabetes can cause skin changes and increase the risk of thermal injuries."],"references":["Bodman MA, Dreyer MA, Varacallo M. Diabetic Peripheral Neuropathy. 2024 Feb 25. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 28723038.","Feldman EL, Callaghan BC, Pop-Busui R, Zochodne DW, Wright DE, Bennett DL, Bril V, Russell JW, Viswanathan V. Diabetic neuropathy. Nat Rev Dis Primers. 2019 Jun 13;5(1):42. doi: 10.1038/s41572-019-0097-9. PMID: 31197183; PMCID: PMC7096070.","Singh, V. (2024). Textbook of Clinical Neuroanatomy-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Michael-Titus, A. T., \u0026 Shortland, P. (2022). The Nervous System, E-Book: The Nervous System, E-Book. Elsevier Health Science","Merryman J, Varacallo M. Klumpke Palsy. 2023 Aug 4. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30285395"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61377"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17549"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61377","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/61377"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-01T05:11:41+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-01T05:11:41+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10239"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75864"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4911","links":{"self":"https://app.e